defaultSyria
default was imposed in May 2011. That was when the first sanctions were imposed, and between that time and the end of 2011, there were 10 amendments to those sanctions, so there were continuous discussions about actual sanctions, potential sanctions and some of those discussions came to nothing. At one point, there were discussions about possible sanctions on the export of phosphates to 
defaultSyria
